# AI Agent Roles & Workflow
- **Planning Mode (Primary: Claude)**: When I ask for a "Plan", provide a detailed checklist of changes. Explain the "Why" behind each step. Focus on Laravel architecture and clean logic.
- **Execution Mode (Primary: Gemini)**: After a plan is approved, use the "Composer" to implement changes. Strictly adhere to the proposed plan while maintaining project standards.
- **Separation**: Do not mix planning and coding in the same response unless specifically asked.
- **Cross-Model Execution**: When Gemini implements a plan generated by Claude, it must respect all architectural decisions made in the plan.




# UI & Laravel Skills (Frontend Specialist)
- **Zero-Frontend Policy**: I don't work on Frontend. When I paste Tailwind HTML, automatically refactor it for Laravel.
- **Dark Theme Wrapper**: IMPORTANT! Always wrap the content inside `<div class="bg-slate-900 min-h-screen p-8 text-white">` before putting it inside `<x-layout>`. This ensures Tailwind UI components are visible.
- **Blade Component Standard**: Always wrap the final code in `<x-layout :title="$page_title">`.
- **Input Styling**: All form inputs must use: `bg-white/5 border-white/10 text-white focus:ring-indigo-500 rounded-md`.
- **Labels**: All labels must be `text-sm font-medium text-white`.

# Logic & Validation
- **Form Essentials**: Always add `@csrf` to every `<form>`.
- **Validation Persistence**: Every input field must include:
    1. `@error('fieldname')` with a `text-red-500 text-xs` message.
    2. `value="{{ old('fieldname') }}"` for data persistence.
- **Dynamic Content**: Replace all static placeholders (like "Jane Doe") with Blade variables or placeholders like `{{ $placeholder }}`.



# Laravel Skills
- I don't do Frontend. When I paste Tailwind HTML, automatically refactor it for Laravel.
# General Coding & UI Standards
- **Component Consistency**: Any UI element requested in Chat must follow the Tailwind UI Dark theme.
- **Input Styling**: All form inputs must have the class `bg-white/5 border-white/10 text-white focus:ring-indigo-500` by default.
- **Label Styling**: Labels should always be `text-sm font-medium text-white`.
- **Validation**: Automatically append `@error('fieldname') <span class="text-red-500 text-xs">{{ $message }}</span> @enderror` to every input you create.
- **Layout Persistence**: Never generate code without the `<x-layout>` and the dark background wrapper we defined.